inn1.comm: just a bit of late inswing and well defended on the front foot by Watson, one slip in place
just goes back and across and punches it down to cover
that one really jags back in off a good length and traps him on the hip but above the line of the stumps
curves it back in and he tucks it softly towards short midwicket
stays behind the line and softly taps it to mid-on, the ball's not coming on all the quick onto the bat
nice square drive to get off the mark, Praveen swings it away and but lands it too full and wide, enough time for Watson to get on his knees and place it wide of backward point
angles it on the pads and he nudges it down to fine leg
bowls it back of a length outside off and he moves across and taps it to cover
bowls it fuller and slower, shapes to drive straight but he gets an inside edge to the on side
drifts on the pads this time and it's an easy nudge to fine leg who's quite square
commits to the front foot fairly early and it works for Ponting as he shows the full face of the bat and merely pushes it past the gap at cover, exquisite timing carries it to the boundary
slower ball angling away from the right-hander, he leaves it alone and the ball bounces again before reaching the keeper
on target, swings it in and Watson defends with soft hands
firm punch off the front foot and intercepted by the bowler
cramps him for room and gets late swing, once again he defends with soft hands
gives him just a hint of width and this time he gets beside the line and softly taps it to point
stays back and punches it to mid-off, inswing this time
and he ends with a maiden, another punch straight to mid-off
keeps a wee bit low and Ponting gets forward early and defends back to the bowler
stays beside the line and knocks it down to point
once again the ball stops on Ponting a bit as he gets beside it and chops it to point
nice timing, he angles it across the right hander, Ponting gets beside the line, opens the face of the bat and uses his bottom hand to good effect to angle it just wide of third man
slower ball on the pads and tucked just wide of mid-on, nice stop by the fielder
drops it on a good length just outside off, he gets across his stumps and taps it to mid-off
he drops it short of a length and once again it stops on the batsman, he gets across early and then has to check his shot
gets behind the line and defends it away
swings it in, tucks him up for room, he gets across and taps it down to mid-on
a slip would have gobbled that up, he opens the face of the bat to a slower ball and deliberately angles it wide of the keeper, third man mops up
gets forward and taps it to the off side
angles it towards the pads and knocks it down to deep square leg
it's a direct hit but the batsman's home, he taps it to mid-on, they push for the single and Raina hits the stumps at the bowler's end but watson's safe
Appeal! Ponting defends very close to his pads and it appeared as if it was pad first and then bat, close call but fair enough decision by Sanjay Hazare
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side
gets well forward and defends softly down the track
he shapes to bang that through the off side and he ends up chopping it down to short point
stays back and pushes it to the off side
terrific shot! Drops it just short of a length and slightly wide of the off stump, the bounce was just right for Watson to show the full face of the bat and punch it effortlessly wide of mid-off
angles it towards the pads and he clips it down to mid-on
stays beside the line and taps it towards cover
the off cutter this time, he tries to tuck it to the on side but the ball clips his pads
drops it a bit too short and Ponting swivels, gets on top of the bounce and pulls it wide of midwicket
drifts on the pads and Ponting helps it on its way down to fine leg
stays back and pushes it down to mid-off
keeps it just outside the off stump and he's content pushing it down to mid-off
another backfoot punch down the track and mid-off runs across to pick it up
lands it on target just outside the off stump and he knocks it down to midwicket
all you need to do is find the gap and that's exactly what Ponting did so effortlessly, a defensive push off the front foot through the line was enough to beat mid-on, lovely shot
gets forward and pushes it straight to the covers
he nearly concedes a boundary there, friendly half volley on the pads and he clips it away but finds Tendulkar at short midwicket, sharp save
gives him width and he tries to cut past backward point but he finds the fielder
drifts on the pads and he clips him to fine leg
good improvisation there by Watson as he gets forward, waits for the ball to come onto him before angling him down to third man
stays back and pushes it down the track just wide of the bowler, pinches a single
shuffles and clips it

excellent fielding there, Nehra comes round the wicket and Watson fetches it from the off stump, clips him uppishly and the ball races towards the midwicket boundary but Praveen gives the chase, times his dive well and pulls it back
Watson tucks it to mid wicket, straight to the fielder this time
stays behind the line and clips him down to mid-on
flighted on middle and leg and he works it down to wide long-on
this one really grips off the surface and has the batsman in a tangle, he checks his shot and the outside edge beats first slip
crisp timing there, he flights it on middle and leg, Watson gets his bat and weight behind the ball and merely pushes it past mid-on, the ball races away
stays back and knocks it to the off side
gets beside the line and angles it just wide of point
gets forward a little early and Ponting taps it just wide of point and sets off
keeps it straight and around the off stump, the batsman's happy to defend it back to the bowler
clips it just in  front of mid-on  and really puts pressure on the fielder by calling quickly for the single, the throw is wide
sharp single again, he opens the face and angles it with soft hands just wide of point and the throw to the batsman's end it just wide
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side, they take a single
gets behind the line and defends
flighted outside off and defended with soft hands to the off side
grips and straightens, he defends it away
almost an edge! The ball grips and turns this time, the batsman tries to push it to the off side but the turn beats him
defends it easily to the off side this time
shot! He drops it fractionally short this time, fetches it from the off stumps and clubs it wide of midwicket
clips him down to deep square leg and pushes for the second run
drifts on the pads and it's not recommended when the fine leg's up, he clips it away and Harbhajan pulls it back
gets behind the line and tries to drive but he mistimes the shot
opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
gets behind the line and defends very firmly
full on the pads and asking to be hit, he ends up clipping it straight to midwicket
that's a super shot, he drops it on a good length and Watson picks the length early, gets on top of the bounce and slaps it in the air in the gap between mid-on and midwicket
gets forward and drives to mid-off
stays beside the line and cuts him down to point
goes on the backfoot to defend
appeal! Gets forward to defend and it's pad first, maybe struck him just outside the line of the off stump
gets well forward and defends to the off side
slow through the air, defends with soft hands
Quicker through the air and defended easily
gets forward and clips him down to midwicket
flighted on middle and off and defended back to the bowler
stays back, shuffles and works him behind square on the on side
drops it in front of midwicket and hurries the single, the throw was just wide of the stumps
stays back and taps him down to mid-off

sharp work by Dhoni! Yuvraj tosses it up outside off and draws Watson forward, he's beaten on the drive, the ball holds its line and Dhoni whips off the bails before the batsman can draw his backfoot back at the crease, the third umpire takes a look, Dhoni knew he was gone the instant he broke the stumps
gets forward and drives to mid-off
flighted outside off and clipped to midwicket
stays back and pushes it against the turn to mid-on
gets forward and clips him straight to short midwicket
gets forward and smothers the spin
gives it extra flight and Ponting takes a pace forward and drives with the spin to long-on
flighted on middle and leg and clipped to midwicket
flighted on middle and leg, he tucks him down to fine leg
gets forward and steers it just in front of backward point and takes the single easily
ouch! Gambhir intercepts a full blooded pull at forward short leg and he gets hit on the neck, he's going off the field, 'neck guards' anyone?
flighted on middle and off, he drives to mid-off
gets forward and clips him to mid-on
gets well forward and drives him down to long-off
pinches a quick single to the off side, he's doing this easily
gets forward and drives him down to mid-off
full outside off and driven down to cover
gets forward and works him down to deep midwicket
gets forward and pushes it just wide of midwicket
gets well across his stumps to defend, the ball rolls down the pitch
gets across his stumps early and clips him down to fine leg
gets forward and defends to the off side
gets forward, drops his wrists and defends with soft hands
gets well forward and angles it down to point
gets across and taps him down to point
gets forward and defends to the on side
stays back and punches it with the turn to long-on
drops it to short midwicket and sets off
punches it to the off side but can't pierce cover
flighted outside off and pushed away down to long-on
gets forward and tucks him to the on side
tries to pinch it past square leg but finds the fielder
full outside off and driven to point
gets well forward and defends with a dead bat
floated on the pads and clipped down to fine leg
flighted on middle and off, defended on the front foot
gets a huge stride forward and defends
stays back and punches it straight to short cover
full outside off and defended
gets his front foot across his stumps and clips him wide of midwicket
clips him on the up straight to short midwicket
flighted on middle and leg and clipped down to fine leg
full outside off and driven down to long-off
drives wide of cover and Hussey hurries the fielder and takes the second run, good cricket by the Australians
knocks it in in front of point and sets off quickly, very good running
comes down the track and chips it over midwicket
gets forward and turns it to mid-on
full outside off and he drives down to long-off
flighted on middle and leg and knocked to midwicket
gets forward, turns the face of the bat and clips him to fine leg
stays back and knocks him down to deep cover
rocks on the backfoot and punches it on the up towards short cover
stays back and clips him down to midwicket
goes on the backfoot and cuts him down to deep point and that's his fifty
gets forward and knocks him down to square leg
stays back and works it to long-on, he walks the single
defended back to the bowler
gets well forward and smothers the spin
tries to work it past the bowler but Yuvraj intercepts it with his left hand
gets in position early for the paddle sweep, picks it from middle and places it to fine leg
chance? Ponting tries to paddle it but he;s into the shot too early and the ball clips something, lobs up and Dhoni dives in vain in front of the stumps, he fails to get his gloves underneath it
goes back and scoops it over extra cover
gets his pad across and clips him down to square leg
comes down the pitch to a short ball and changes his shot, pulls off the front foot but can't bisect the gap at square leg
clips it behind square but can't beat short fine leg
overthrows! The batsmen decided against the run  but an enthusiastic Raina at mid-off takes aim at the bowler's end but no backers for the throw
gets across and clips him behind square on the on side
stays back and thumps him down to sweeper cover
plays the reverse sweep and Harbhajan does well at short fine leg to cut it off
the ball keeps low but he goes ahead with the shot and lofts him over mid-off
full outside off, driven down to long off
gets forward and smothers the spin
stays back, waits for the ball to come into him before thumping it to long-off
full on middle and leg and driven down to long-on
stays back, waits for it to turn and pulls him down to deep square-leg
tries to fetch it from wide outside off but he misses it completely
pushes it just wide of the bowler and fetches a single
stays back and punches it back to the bowler
gives him width and he reaches out and cuts to third man
gets behind the line and the swing and punches it off the meat of the bat to long-on
he just opens the face of the bat and angles him down to third man
stays back and punches him down to long-on
opens the face of the bat and angles it down to third man
covers the swing and pushes him down to long-on
trapped in front! Jadeja fires it full and quick on middle, Ponting tries to clip it across the line but the ball hits the base of the pads (close to the boot) right in front of the stumps
Pushed back to the bowler
Pushed back to the bowler
Pushes it down the track again
stays back and pushes it back to the bowler
grips and turns sharply and Hussey manages to check his shot and not spoon it back to the bowler
full outside off and driven down to long-off
bowls it flatter and quicker, he works it back to the bowler

it appears as if White's got a rough decision there. Raina bowls it flat again and White leaves a small gap between bat and pad, it almost sneaks right through before reaching Dhoni who juggles and appeals for the catch, umpire Saheba gives him out, replays confirm the ball clipping the pad but no real evidence of bat involved, White was quite surprised at the decision
pushed back to the bowler
steers it towards point
gets forward and steers the ball towards gully
played with soft hands back towards the bowler
keeps it full outside off, dug out towards short cover
another overpitched delivery, driven just wide of the bowler towards long-off
that kept very low, Hussey manages to get the toe end of the bat on it and drive it towards mid-on
'No' is the call after Voges pushes the ball towards cover
full delivery just outside off, nudged towards backward point off the back foot
turns into the pads, clipped towards square leg
straighter one this time, defended to the leg side
a bit of width outside off, chopped towards point
Hussey stays on the backfoot and plays the ball late, it was angling into his pads, whipped towards wide mid-on
watchfully defends a length ball pitching just outside off to end the over
'Two, two, two' Hussey shouts after he whips the ball off the backfoot towards long-on, well-timed shot that, Harbhajan had to dive at the boundary to cut it off
dinks it past the keeper towards third man, very fine so Tendulkar had to make plenty of ground to field that one
gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it back towards the bowler
full ball on the pads, tucked behind square leg for yet another single
and a long boundary-less streak comes to an end as Voges checks his paddle-sweep to get the ball very fine down the leg side
full and outside off, blocked towards point
on the pads, was going down leg so there's only a stifled appeal for lbw
rocks onto the backfoot and carves the ball past cover, Sehwag misfields to give away four
eased to long-on for an easy single
defended towards midwicket
the 150 comes up with a single to long-on, Voges danced down th track to drill that one down the ground
Hussey gets on the backfoot and turns the ball towards midwicket as he has so many times this innings to get a single
and again, Hussey gets on the back foot and nudges the ball towards midwicket for a single
Voges get two by hacking the ball wide of Praveen Kumar at deep midwicket
gets the outside edge, the ball drops short of first slip though
punched towards mid-on for a single
superb shot from Hussey, sees the gap at point, and brings out the reverse-sweep to exploit that, kept the ball all along the ground  that time
stands tall and jabs the ball towards mid-on
flicked off the backfoot towards square leg
length ball on middle and leg, eased down to long-on for a single
length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler, who mimes throwing down the stumps after collecting the ball
Hussey advances down the pitch, clips the ball behind square leg for a single
full, on middle and off, defended towards mid-on this time
slower ball, 114kmh, Hussey had to adjust his attempted flick, gets a thick inside edge onto his thigh
Harbhajan's first ball is pushed back to the bowler
fires it down the leg side, way beyond leg
the ball continues to keep low, Voges happy to play off the backfoot, turns the ball towards square leg
Hussey also rocks back and drives the ball towards cover
a bit of width this time, Hussey slashes it past point
sharp turn for Harbhajan, Voges gets on the front foot and clips the ball towards short fine leg
good running that, Voges gets a big stride in and dabs the ball towards point, immediately sets off for the single
Hussey gets to his half-century by making room and guiding the ball past the keeper towards third man, sensible batting so far from Hussey
beaten outside off, Voges jumps out of the crease and looks to dab that to third man
back of a length ball, just outside off, punched towards cover, Voges walked into that shot
Hussey uses his feet, Ishant drops it short, Hussey is cramped for room, whips the ball towards wide mid-on
slower offcutter from Ishant to end the over, 113.5kmh, nudged towards midwicket
Hussey backs away and plays the ball inside out towards extra cover
sweeps a full ball from outside off towards deep backward square leg
another ball way down the leg side from Harbhajan
a loud call of 'No' from Voges after a solid forward defensive
looks the give the charge, it was a shortish ball, blocks it after coming down the pitch
Harbhajan Singh gets a wicket, Voges sashays down the track and slams the ball with the spin towards deep midwicket, Praveen hangs on to a good catch
an unflustered Hussey continues to pick off the singles, this time by tapping a full ball towards long-on
another single to Hussey, this time he steers the ball to short third man
gets off the mark by tipping the ball to the off side and immediately responding to Hussey's call for a single
Hussey is again content to dab an outside-off ball towards third man for a single
Henriques takes a leaf out of the Hussey book, he also guides the ball to third man for an easy single
a yorker just outside off, swinging in, Hussey squeezes it behind point
stands tall and punches a short of length ball from offstump towards mid-off, 'No' is the batsman's call but a misfield allows them the single
Henriques lunges forward to defend, the turn causes an inside edge which sends the ball towards square leg
on the pads, Hussey plays it with soft hands towards square leg, superb running from Hussey, sprinting the first to put pressure on the fielder, Harbhajan screams at the fielder
pitched outside off, and turned sharply away, Hussey crashes that towaqrds backward point, Sehwag dives to his left to field that one
Henriques wanted the single after dropping the ball at his feet, Dhoni was quickly onto the ball
another dot ball, a middle stump delivery is defended to the leg side
Henriques didn't know much about that one, it spun away sharply beating his attempted defense, runs away down the leg side, beats the keeper as well
tosses the ball up, dropped towards backward point for a single
slightly overpitched on middle stump, worked towards square leg for another single
full and outside off, slogged towards deep midwicket for yet another single
length ball heading for off, the batsman backs away and carves it towards cover
fifth consecutive single in the over, paddle-swept this time
completes an over of single by slashing the ball towards cover
'Two, two, two' Hussey cries after Henriques punches the ball wide of long-on, Hussey was so quick that the throw had to go all the way to the keeper's end
Henriques has to put the skates on again, a full ball on the pads and he pushes it towards mid-on, the throw misses though
length ball on middle and off, Hussey shuffles across and whips it to deep midwicket
good over so far from Nehra, pitches this one short of a length, blocked back to the bowler, Hussey was backing up a long way, had to dive back into his crease
another shortish ball, follows the batsman as Henriques skips away from legstump, no room for the batsman who somehow gets the ball away towards square leg
Hussey goes for a cute paddle-sweep to a full ball outside off, it sneaks under his bat, Dhoni has a tough take as the ball bounces just before it reaches him
Henriques backs away a long way, had plenty of room as he looked to smash that over extra cover, gets a bottom-edge back towards the bowler
skips away again, carves this one to sweeper cover, good throw from Praveen, right on top of the stumps but Henriques was quick enough to make his ground in time
fires this one towards legstump, Henriques moves away from leg yet again, gets a bottom edge as he looks to slam that through the off, the ball bounces once before hitting legstump
fullish ball, jammed back towards the bowler
looks to cut a ball that is just outside off, but he doesn't make contact
and again he doesn't get bat on ball, it goes through to Dhoni outside off, a great over from Jadeja that
Hussey's favourite slog-pull gets Australia a much-needed boundary, picks it off a length and slams it wide off deep midwicket
same shot from Hussey, no as much power behind it this time, Kohli scurries across from deep midwicket to field
on middle and leg, nudges it towards square leg for a single
just short of length, on off, punched back to the bowler
looks to swing the ball to the leg side, it was a touch slower from Nehra, Johnson was through with his shot too early, no contact
fuller ball outside off, Johnson again looks to club it towards midwicket, misses
length ball on middle and leg, clipped towards midwicket to bring Johnson on strike
this time Johnson connects, and when he does connect well it's usually a six, it sails over long-on after coming down the track and slamming it against the spin
looks for an encore, mishit towards mid-on
very short from Raina, Hussey was way down the track, punches the ball towards long-on
a powerful reverse-sweep from Johnson, Yuvraj dives full length to his right at point to cut it off
looked to clobber it to long-on again, gets an outside edge which sends the ball trickling towards short third man
a massive six, short ball, danced down the track, pulled wide of long-on
way down the leg side, he'll have to re-bowl that one
much fuller this time, Hussey looks for the big swing, gets an inside-edge onto his pads, he's not sure where it's gone, it's at his feet, they take a single anyway
swing and a miss from Johnson, slightly short from Nehra, the midwicket boundary was in Johnson's radar
skips away from leg and bludgeons the ball along the ground to long-on for a single
full and well outside off, Hussey digs it out towards cover
goes for the paddle-sweep, is hit on the pads outside off, the ball dribbles towards leg gully

inn2.comm: hits a good length on leg and he shuffles and clips him down to fine leg
poor delivery down the leg side and Sachin shoulders arms
gets a bit of late swing and he turns the face of the bat to clip it wide of midwicket
uppish but safe, he drops it short of a length in the off stump and gets it to angle away, Tendulkar reaches out, plays away from the body and punches it in the gap between backward point and cover
angles it across the right hander and he lets it go
gets a nice stride forward and defends
terrific shot, 149 kph, he angles it towards the body and Tendulkar shuffles and uses the pace of the ball to clip it effortlessly past square leg, fine leg chases in vain
angles it into the right hander and he tucks it just wide of mid-on
keeps a wee but low but Tendulkar easily gets behind it and defends with soft hands
147.7 kph, pacy delivery and angles it just on that corridor outside off, well left by Tendulkar, good cricket
keeps it on a good length on middle and leg and he pushes it down to mid-on
fullish in length and he gets a generous stride forward to defend it
gets it to kick up off a good length and he taps it wide of short cover for a single
loses his line and dishes it wide outside off, close to being called a wide, the ball bounces twice before reaching the keeper
reaches out and this time he gets a thick outside edge to third man
too close to cut and he nearly edges it to the keeper, extra bounce there for Johnson
drops it just in front of mid-on and sets off, well run
hops at the crease to a short delivery and times the clip very well past square leg,
he drifts on the body again and it's too easy for Tendulkar as he works it down to fine leg, not the best line to bowl I'm afraid
Times the punch really well but finds short cover
Angles it outside off and he opens the face of the bat and angles it to third man
150 kph, Siddle matches Johnson for pace, Sehwag gets beside the line and steers it to point
tempts him with width and he can't resist a swish, lucky not to get an edge
meets the ball from outside off and clips it across the line to midwicket
drifts close to the pads and Tendulkar nearly clips it past short fine leg, the fielder misfields but deep square does well to run across and slide to cut it off
stays behind the line and defends to the off side
cramps him for room outside off and he tries to slice it through the off side but can't beat cover
147.9 kph, seemed faster than that, excellent bouncer, forces Sehwag to sway out of the way just in time
fuller in length outside off, he can't resist a whack and the outside edge travels fast to third man
gets behind the line and defends to the off side
gets beside the line this time and steers it to point
stays behind the line and defends back to the bowler
defended on the backfoot again
fullish outside off and in the length to drive, he pushes it down to point
gets beside the line and steers it down to third man
he gets a thick outside edge which drops short of White at first slip, he should be standing a lot closer
lands it outside off and he safely shoulders arms
he gets behind the line to a full delivery and drives to cover
Sehwag eyes a blazing drive past backward point and nearly succeeds in beating that fielder, good stop in the end
he loses his direction and drifts towards the body, he clips it away easily to get off strike
gets beside the line and taps it to the off side
fuller and wider and he mistimes it to point
lovely straight drive off a half volley but mid-off was right at the edge of the circle to cut it off
angles it towards the leg side and he shuffles and works it down to fine leg
lands just outside the off stump and gets it to come back in, solid in defense again
fullish in length outside off and he times it crisply past cover, good effort by the fielder to pull it back
keeps just a bit low but he manages to push it away easily to the off side
Appeal Fires it on the blockhole down the leg side and that hits Sehwag on the boot down the leg side, confident appeal and Saheba shakes his head, Sehwag's in pain and the physio walks out
angles it on middle and leg and easily clipped away down to square leg
clips a full delivery just wide of square leg, there's a misfield
Sehwag breaks the shackles, just the sort of delivery he was waiting for, short and wide outside off and slapped over backward point, forget about chasing that
tries to repeat that boundary but Johnson varies his pace and Sehwag swishes at thin air

timber! The middle stump is flattened, Johnson lands it in a good length on middle and off, Sehwag is trapped at the crease, he tries to work it across the line but leaves a big gap between bat and pad, the ball sneaks right through and takes out the middle stump which lands a couple of yards back
good start, gets right behind the line and defends back to the bowler
gets forward and drives to point
gets behind the line and defends
holds the length back slightly and he gets beside the line and steers it down to point
fullish in length outside off and he gets forward and pushes it down to point
hits the deck hard and Tendulkar does well to get his bat nicely behind the line to defend
nice backfoot punch, the fielder at cover dives to his right and parries the ball away, Hauritz runs across to field it
opens the face of the bat and steers it down to Siddle at third man
angles it away from the right hander, he gets forward and pushes it wide of cover
suspect short there, he stays rooted to the crease and chases a delivery moving away from him, beaten all ends up
excellent running by Tendulkar, the minute Gambhir dropped it with soft hands to the off side his partner was off the blocks very quickly
pitches it full and gets a bit of late swing, he gets forward and taps it down to mid-off
drops it on a good length on the off stump, Tendulkar hops and defends
opens the face of the bat and angles it down to Siddle at third man
Gambhir stays at the crease, drops his wrists and knocks it towards gully with soft hands and sets off
shapes to drive straight but mistimes the shot back to the bowler
gets forward and drives firmly towards point who dives and parries the ball away
Lands outside leg and traps him high on the pads, Bollinger appeals
beaten all ends up, the ball lands outside off and fizzes past the outside edge, pacy delivery there
stays beside the line and taps it towards cover
angles it towards the pads and he closes the face of the bat and works it to square leg
gets beside the line and cuts firmly down to backward point
just a touch too full and he places it just wide of short cover, nice timing

he's run out by a couple of yards, Johnson hits the target, he pushes a full delivery down to mid-off and risks the single, the ball is to Johnson's left and that allows him to gather and release it quickly, the run-out was fairly obvious, the umpire confirms with the man upstairs. Tendulkar in fact had to run around the bowler so he lost a precious second or two there
opens the face of the bat and angles it down to third man
keeps a but low and he taps it to the off side
gets well forward and pushes it to the off side
outside off and he pokes at it
stays beside the line and knocks it down to cover point
drops it short of a length outside off, he opens the face of the bat and angles it down to third man
testing inswinging yorker, Yuvraj gets a thick inside edge onto his pads and nearly loses his balance, well bowled and Bollinger appeals for a lbw
catches him fishing outside the off stump with a beautiful in-dipper
swings it in again and he pushes it through the line to mid-on
Not much turn, lands on middle and off and he defends

What a ball! Gambhir was just flummoxed, Hauritz lands it on a good length on middle, the ball grips, turns and beats the gap between pad and bat and clips the off stump, Gambhir looked quite lost at the crease and barely attempted to clip it across the line
gets well forward and defends
bonus for India, the ball keeps low, lands outside leg and beats everybody, five wides
pushes it to point off the backfoot
stays back and punches him down to cover for a single
